# Copy to signing.env (gitignored) or set in CI secrets — NEVER commit the real .pfx or password.
#
# Windows code signing for production installers (fixes SmartScreen / Smart App Control blocks).
#
# CSC_LINK — absolute path to your Authenticode certificate (.pfx), OR a base64-encoded pfx string in CI.
# CSC_KEY_PASSWORD — private key password from your certificate provider.
#
# Optional (only if your CA requires it):
# CSC_NAME — subject name on the certificate, e.g. "AsbaTechs Pvt Ltd"
#
# Example (local build machine):
# CSC_LINK=C:\certs\asbatechs-code-signing.pfx
# CSC_KEY_PASSWORD=your-certificate-password
#
# Then from monorepo root:
#   npm run build:desktop:signed
#
# Output: apps/desktop/release/AsbaTechs CRM Setup x.x.x.exe (signed)

CSC_LINK=
CSC_KEY_PASSWORD=
